    {
      "id": "views-authoring-step-1",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 1",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 40
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 1: Adopt Stable View Payload Names (Contract)\n\nWhy:\n- The `payload` string is the stable discovery + selection API for ports.\n\nUse these payloads consistently:\n- `node.web.icon`\n- `node.web.summary` (required for port-style consumption)\n- `node.web.detail`\n- `node.web.document`\n- `editor.web` (editors only)\n\nRule of thumb:\n- Ports consume **only** `node.web.*` surfaces.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "views-authoring-step-2",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 2",
      "position": {
        "x": 340,
        "y": 40
      },
      "width": 640,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 2: Create A Port-Consumable Surface (node.web.summary)\n\nIn a target graph (or node class graph), add a view node that can render without running code.\n\nMinimum requirements for a port-consumable surface:\n- A view node with:\n  - `payload` = `node.web.summary`\n  - editable content fields (at least `title` and optionally `purpose` / `svg`)\n\nSuggested primitive:\n- Use the `summary-view` node type, setting:\n  - `payload`: `node.web.summary`\n  - `viewRole`: `summary`\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "views-authoring-step-3",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 3",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 340
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 3: Add An Editor Surface (editor.web)\n\nWhy:\n- Authors need a consistent way to edit the surface node data.\n\nImplementation:\n- Add a view node with:\n  - `intent` = `editor`\n  - `payload` = `editor.web`\n- Use structured fields (`editor.web.fields[]`) to map UI controls to node data paths.\n\nMinimum editor fields worth having:\n- `data.title`\n- `data.purpose`\n- `data.svg`\n- `data.payload` (select)\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "views-authoring-step-4",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 4",
      "position": {
        "x": 340,
        "y": 380
      },
      "width": 640,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 4: Consume The Surface From A Port\n\nOpen the demo graph:\n- `/tutorial/views-surface-demo.document.node#root`\n\nIn a separate consumer graph:\n1) Add a **Port** node\n2) Set its target ref to the demo graph\n3) Ensure it is consuming views (not providing its own)\n4) Use the view selector dropdown to choose:\n   - `node.web.summary` (default)\n   - `node.web.detail`\n   - `node.web.icon`\n\nExpected:\n- Switching the consumed view changes what the port renders.\n- The selector stays stable (same options every time you open it).\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "views-authoring-step-5",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 5",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 720
      },
      "width": 1240,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Expected Result\n\n- You can author a `node.web.summary` surface as a node.\n- The surface remains editable via `editor.web` fields.\n- Ports can discover and consume port-style views (`node.web.*`) and switching payloads changes rendering.\n- View payload names stay standardized across graphs so discovery is predictable."
      }
    }
  ],
